Police in Mutale near Thohoyandou have launched a manhunt for three armed men who robbed and killed a local businessman, Limpopo police said on Saturday. It was alleged that the 42-year-old businessman was sleeping in his shop at about 10.30pm on Friday when he was attacked, robbed of groceries and cellphones, and shot dead by assailants who then fled the scene. Anyone with any information about the robbers should please contact the Mutale Police Station on 082-565-8149 or 015-967-8000, or the nearest police station, or the crime stop number 08600-10111, or the 24-hour crime line sms 32211. ALSO READ: Fatal Soweto shooting possibly linked to taxi violence African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.